{
  "id": "builtin-0604",
  "name": "0604 每日词汇整理",
  "version": "2026-06-06",
  "source": "0604.docx",
  "group": "0529-0604",
  "entries": [
    {
      "id": "0604-reckoned",
      "term": "reckoned",
      "meaning": "v. / adj.；认为；估计；料想。",
      "morph": "reckon 表示“认为、估计、计算”；-ed 表示过去式或过去分词。",
      "example": "搭配：reckon that... 认为……；be reckoned at... 被估计为……；例句：I reckoned he was right. 我认为他是对的。；提醒：偏口语，意思接近 thought / believed / estimated。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "基础表达",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-go-along",
      "term": "go along",
      "meaning": "phr.；继续进行；进展；配合。",
      "morph": "go 表示“走、进行”；along 表示“沿着、一起、继续”。",
      "example": "搭配：go along with sb/sth 同意、配合、赞成。；例句：I will go along with your plan. 我会同意你的计划。；提醒：with 后接人或计划，表示“跟着走、配合”。",
      "type": "phrase",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "基础表达",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-secretary",
      "term": "secretary",
      "meaning": "n.；秘书；干事；部长；大臣。",
      "morph": "secret 表示“秘密”；-ary 表示“与……有关的人或物”。原意接近“处理秘密事务的人”。",
      "example": "搭配：a company secretary 公司秘书；Secretary of State 国务卿/外交部长。；例句：She works as a secretary. 她是一名秘书。；提醒：在政府语境中不一定是“秘书”，常指高级官员。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "基础表达",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-slides",
      "term": "slides",
      "meaning": "n. / v.；幻灯片；滑梯；滑动；下降。",
      "morph": "slide 表示“滑动；幻灯片”；-s 表示复数或第三人称单数。",
      "example": "搭配：presentation slides 演示文稿；price slides 价格下滑。；例句：I made ten slides for my presentation. 我为演讲做了十页幻灯片。；提醒：在学习和汇报场景中通常指 PPT 页面。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "基础表达",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-as-to",
      "term": "as to",
      "meaning": "prep. phr.；关于；至于；就……而言。",
      "morph": "as 表示“就……而言”；to 表示“指向某对象”。",
      "example": "搭配：as to whether... 至于是否……；as to his plan 关于他的计划。；例句：There is some doubt as to whether he will come. 至于他是否会来，还有些疑问。；提醒：接近 about / regarding / concerning，语气稍正式。",
      "type": "phrase",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "基础表达",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-remark",
      "term": "remark",
      "meaning": "n. / v.；评论；话语；说；谈到。",
      "morph": "re- 表示“再次、回头”；mark 表示“标记、注意”。可理解为“说出观察到的东西”。",
      "example": "搭配：make a remark 发表评论；remark that... 说……；例句：His remark made me angry. 他的话让我生气。；提醒：作动词时比 say 更正式，强调“评论、指出”。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "基础表达",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-dramatic",
      "term": "dramatic",
      "meaning": "adj.；戏剧性的；巨大的；显著的；激动人心的。",
      "morph": "drama 表示“戏剧”；-tic/-atic 是形容词后缀，表示“……的”。",
      "example": "搭配：a dramatic increase 大幅增加；a dramatic change 巨大变化。；例句：There has been a dramatic increase in prices. 价格出现了大幅上涨。；提醒：考试中常取“显著的、巨大的”这一含义。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "商业经济",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-extend",
      "term": "extend",
      "meaning": "v.；延长；扩展；伸出；提供。",
      "morph": "ex- 表示“向外”；tend/tens 表示“伸展、拉伸”。",
      "example": "搭配：extend the deadline 延长期限；extend help 提供帮助。；例句：They decided to extend the deadline. 他们决定延长期限。；提醒：相关词：extension 延长；extensive 广泛的；extent 程度。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "商业经济",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-retailers",
      "term": "retailers",
      "meaning": "n.；零售商；零售企业。",
      "morph": "retail 表示“零售”；-er 表示“做某事的人或机构”；-s 表示复数。",
      "example": "搭配：online retailers 网上零售商；major retailers 大型零售商。；例句：Online retailers are attracting more customers. 网上零售商正在吸引更多顾客。；提醒：对比 wholesaler 批发商；consumer 消费者。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "商业经济",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-rivals",
      "term": "rivals",
      "meaning": "n. / v.；竞争对手；与……竞争；可与……匹敌。",
      "morph": "rival 表示“竞争者、对手；与……竞争”；-s 表示复数或第三人称单数。",
      "example": "搭配：business rivals 商业竞争对手；rival sb in sth 在某方面匹敌某人。；例句：The two companies are fierce rivals. 这两家公司是激烈的竞争对手。；提醒：既可作名词，也可作动词。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "商业经济",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-ties-up",
      "term": "ties up",
      "meaning": "phr. v.；绑住；系牢；占用；与……合作或有关。",
      "morph": "tie 表示“绑、系、联系”；up 强调“完全、固定住”。",
      "example": "搭配：tie up money 占用资金；tie up with 与……合作。；例句：The project ties up too much money. 这个项目占用了太多资金。；提醒：看到 money/time/resources 时，多理解为“占用”。",
      "type": "phrase",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "商业经济",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-revenue",
      "term": "revenue",
      "meaning": "n.；收入；营收；财政收入。",
      "morph": "re- 表示“回来”；ven/vent 表示“来”。可理解为“回流的钱”。",
      "example": "搭配：annual revenue 年收入；government revenue 政府财政收入。；例句：The company’s revenue increased last year. 公司去年的营收增加了。；提醒：对比 revenue 收入；profit 利润；income 收入。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "商业经济",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-forwarding",
      "term": "forwarding",
      "meaning": "n. / v-ing；转发；推进；货运代理。",
      "morph": "forward 表示“向前；转发”；-ing 表示动名词或现在分词。",
      "example": "搭配：email forwarding 邮件转发；freight forwarding 货运代理。；例句：Thank you for forwarding the email. 谢谢你转发这封邮件。；提醒：商务语境中 freight forwarding 很常见，指货运代理。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "商业经济",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-frantic",
      "term": "frantic",
      "meaning": "adj.；慌乱的；发狂似的；忙乱的。",
      "morph": "可整体记忆；可联想 frenzy 表示“疯狂、狂乱”。",
      "example": "搭配：a frantic search 疯狂寻找；a frantic call 慌乱的电话。；例句：She made a frantic call for help. 她慌乱地打电话求助。；提醒：近义：panicked 惊慌的；desperate 拼命的。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "商业经济",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-refined",
      "term": "refined",
      "meaning": "adj. / v-ed；精炼的；提纯的；改良的；优雅的。",
      "morph": "re- 表示“重新、再次”；fine 表示“细的、精细的”；-ed 构成形容词或过去分词。",
      "example": "搭配：refined sugar 精制糖；refined oil 精炼油。；例句：Too much refined sugar is bad for your health. 过多精制糖对健康不好。；提醒：健康类文章里多指“经过加工提纯的”。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "饮食健康",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-sugars",
      "term": "sugars",
      "meaning": "n.；糖类；各种糖；糖分。",
      "morph": "sugar 表示“糖”；-s 表示复数。",
      "example": "搭配：refined sugars 精制糖；added sugars 添加糖；blood sugar 血糖。；例句：Many soft drinks contain high levels of sugars. 许多软饮含有大量糖分。；提醒：食品标签里的 sugars 常指总糖分。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "饮食健康",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-reserve",
      "term": "reserve",
      "meaning": "n. / v.；保留；预订；储备；保护区；克制。",
      "morph": "re- 可表示“向后、保留”；serve/serv 有“保持、保存”的来源义。可理解为“留在后面备用”。",
      "example": "搭配：reserve a table 预订桌位；oil reserves 石油储备；nature reserve 自然保护区。；例句：We need to reserve some money for emergencies. 我们需要保留一些钱应急。；提醒：reservation 表示“预订；保留意见”。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "饮食健康",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-inclusion",
      "term": "inclusion",
      "meaning": "n.；包含；纳入；包容。",
      "morph": "in- 表示“向内”；clus/clud 表示“关闭”；-ion 是名词后缀。可理解为“把人或物包括进来”。",
      "example": "搭配：social inclusion 社会包容；promote inclusion 促进包容。；例句：The school promotes inclusion of students with different backgrounds. 学校提倡包容不同背景的学生。；提醒：反义相关词：exclusion 排除。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "社会政策",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-prejudiced",
      "term": "prejudiced",
      "meaning": "adj.；有偏见的；带成见的。",
      "morph": "pre- 表示“提前、预先”；judic/judge 表示“判断”；-ed 构成形容词。",
      "example": "搭配：be prejudiced against... 对……有偏见。；例句：He was prejudiced against people from poor families. 他对贫困家庭出身的人有偏见。；提醒：prejudice 是“偏见”；unbiased 是“无偏见的”。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "社会政策",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-nominees",
      "term": "nominees",
      "meaning": "n.；被提名者；候选人；被任命者。",
      "morph": "nom/nomin 表示“名字”；nominate 表示“提名”；-ee 表示“被……的人”；-s 表示复数。",
      "example": "搭配：award nominees 奖项提名人；presidential nominee 总统候选人。；例句：The award nominees were announced yesterday. 奖项提名人昨天公布了。；提醒：nominee 是“被提名的人”，nominator 是“提名者”。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "社会政策",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-policies",
      "term": "policies",
      "meaning": "n.；政策；方针；原则；保险单。",
      "morph": "policy 表示“政策、方针、保险单”；辅音字母+y 结尾变 y 为 i 加 -es。",
      "example": "搭配：education policies 教育政策；company policies 公司制度。；例句：The government introduced new education policies. 政府推出了新的教育政策。；提醒：注意区分 policy 政策；politics 政治；political 政治的。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "社会政策",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-mortgage",
      "term": "mortgage",
      "meaning": "n. / v.；房屋抵押贷款；按揭贷款；抵押。",
      "morph": "mort 表示“死亡”；gage 表示“抵押、担保”。原指一种到期结束或失效的抵押契约。",
      "example": "搭配：mortgage loan 抵押贷款；pay off the mortgage 还清房贷。；例句：They took out a mortgage to buy a house. 他们办了房贷买房。；提醒：生活经济类文章中高频。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "社会政策",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-breadwinner",
      "term": "breadwinner",
      "meaning": "n.；家庭经济支柱；主要挣钱养家的人。",
      "morph": "bread 表示“面包”，引申为“生计、收入”；winner 表示“赢得者、获得者”。合起来是“赢得面包的人”。",
      "example": "搭配：sole breadwinner 唯一经济支柱；family breadwinner 家庭经济支柱。；例句：After his father became ill, he became the family’s breadwinner. 父亲生病后，他成了家里的经济支柱。；提醒：通常合写为 breadwinner，不写成 bread winner。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "社会政策",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-inherently",
      "term": "inherently",
      "meaning": "adv.；本质上；内在地；天生地。",
      "morph": "inherent 表示“内在的、固有的”；-ly 是副词后缀。",
      "example": "搭配：inherently risky 本身有风险；inherently difficult 本来就困难。；例句：The plan is inherently risky. 这个计划本身就有风险。；提醒：接近 by nature / naturally。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "描述表达",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-depiction",
      "term": "depiction",
      "meaning": "n.；描绘；描述；刻画。",
      "morph": "de- 表示“向下、完全”；pict/pic 表示“画、图像”；-ion 是名词后缀。",
      "example": "搭配：a realistic depiction 真实描绘；depiction of war 对战争的描绘。；例句：The film’s depiction of war is very realistic. 这部电影对战争的描绘很真实。；提醒：相关词：depict 描绘；picture 图片、想象。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "描述表达",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-clever",
      "term": "clever",
      "meaning": "adj.；聪明的；巧妙的；机灵的。",
      "morph": "常整体记忆，可理解为“脑子灵活、反应快、办法巧”。",
      "example": "搭配：a clever solution 巧妙的解决办法；a clever trick 聪明的小把戏。；例句：That was a clever solution. 那是一个巧妙的解决办法。；提醒：clever 偏机智；intelligent 偏智力高；smart 偏口语。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "描述表达",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-twist",
      "term": "twist",
      "meaning": "n. / v.；扭动；拧；歪曲；转折；意外变化；情节反转。",
      "morph": "本义是“扭、拧、转”；引申为情节突然转弯，即“反转、转折”。",
      "example": "搭配：a surprising twist 意想不到的反转；twist one’s ankle 扭伤脚踝。；例句：The story has a surprising twist. 这个故事有一个意想不到的反转。；提醒：clever twist 表示“巧妙反转、巧妙设计”。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "描述表达",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-in-excess",
      "term": "in excess",
      "meaning": "phr.；过量地；超过；多于。",
      "morph": "ex- 表示“向外、超过”；cess/ced 表示“走”；excess 可理解为“走出范围”。",
      "example": "搭配：in excess of... 超过……；consume sth in excess 过量摄入某物。；例句：The cost was in excess of 1,000 dollars. 费用超过了1000美元。；提醒：健康类文章中常见：eat/drink/consume in excess。",
      "type": "phrase",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "饮食健康",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-digestive",
      "term": "digestive",
      "meaning": "adj.；消化的；与消化有关的。",
      "morph": "digest 表示“消化、理解”；-ive 是形容词后缀，表示“有……功能的”。",
      "example": "搭配：digestive system 消化系统；digestive problems 消化问题；digestive tract 消化道。；例句：Spicy food may cause digestive problems. 辛辣食物可能导致消化问题。；提醒：digest 作“理解”时，类似“消化知识”。",
      "type": "word",
      "source": "0604.docx",
      "section": "饮食健康",
      "suspectedError": false,
      "warnings": [],
      "audio": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "0604-other-than",
      "term": "other than",
      "meaning": "prep. phr.；除了……之外；不同于；不是。",
      "morph": "other 表示“其他的”；than 表示“比、除……之外”。",
